column12:
Did the Study Conduct Experiments with People Using the Chatbot? (yes or no)

YES: The study included human participants who actually used or interacted with the chatbot system; 
NO: The study DID NOT include human participants who actually used or interacted with the chatbot system;

column17:
Did the Chatbot Have a Human Name? (yes or no)

YES: The chatbot was given a specific human name (e.g. 'Alex' 'Sarah' 'ChatBot Charlie'); 
NO: The chatbot was not given a human name

column18:
Did the Chatbot Have a Gender? (yes or no) 

YES: The chatbot was assigned a specific gender (male female or other); 
NO: The chatbot was not assigned any gender

column19:
Self-Reference Method
How the chatbot refers to itself: 

FIRST-PERSON: Uses 'I' 'me' 'my' (e.g. 'I can help you'); 
THIRD-PERSON: Refers to itself by name or title (e.g. 'ChatBot can help you'); 
NOT MENTIONED: No clear indication of self-reference style

column20:
Visual Representation - How the chatbot appears to users

TEXT-ONLY: Pure text interface with no visual representation; 
AVATAR/EMBODIED: Has a visual character image or 3D representation

column21:
Communication Modality - Primary interaction method

TEXT: Users type and read messages; 
VOICE: Users speak and hear responses; 
MULTIMODAL: Combines text voice and/or other interaction methods

column22:
Backstory Provided for the Bot? (yes or no or no information)

YES: The chatbot was given a personal history background story or fictional biography; 
NO: No backstory was provided;
NO INFORMATION: Paper doesn't mention whether backstory exists

column23:
Was Politeness Encoded in Chatbot Behavior? (yes or no or no information)

YES: The chatbot was specifically programmed to use polite language manners or courteous behavior; 
NO: No specific politeness programming mentioned; 
NO INFORMATION: Paper doesn't address politeness aspects

column24:
Did Chatbot Initiate the Interaction? (yes or no or no information)

YES: The chatbot starts conversations or reaches out to users first;
NO: Users must initiate all interactions; 
NO INFORMATION: Paper doesn't specify who initiates

column25:
Is the Persona of the Chatbot Clearly Mentioned to the User? (Yes or No)

YES: Users are explicitly told about the chatbot's personality traits or persona; 
NO: The persona exists but users are not directly informed about it

column26:
Is the Persona Fixed or Adaptive?

FIXED: The chatbot has the same personality for all users; 
ADAPTIVE: The chatbot's personality changes or adapts based on individual user interactions preferences or contexts

column27:
What Research Methodology is Used?

EMPIRICAL: Studies that collect new data from real people or experiments. ;
CONCEPTUAL: Studies that discuss ideas, theories, or review existing research without collecting new data.

column28:
If the study is empirical, what type of data is used?

QUANTITATIVE: Numerical data statistics measurements; 
QUALITATIVE: Interviews observations text analysis; 
MIXED METHOD: Combines both quantitative and qualitative data

column30:
Was Chatbot Developed for a Real Organization? (yes or no) 

YES: The chatbot was created for an actual company institution or organization; 
NO: The chatbot was developed for research purposes only or is theoretical

column31:
If Chatbot was Developed for a Real Organization 

Who was the Intended User Audience? Complete only if previous answer was YES

PEOPLE INSIDE THE ORGANIZATION: Employees staff or internal users; 
PEOPLE OUTSIDE THE ORGANIZATION: Customers clients or external users; 
PEOPLE BOTH INSIDE AND OUTSIDE THE ORGANIZATION: Mixed audience of internal and external users

column32:
How do Users Interact with Personas?

Primary purpose of interactions: 
ADVISORY: Providing advice guidance or recommendations; 
EDUCATIONAL: Teaching learning or training purposes; 
PROFESSIONAL USE: Work-related tasks or business functions; 
COMPANIONSHIP: Social interaction emotional support or relationship building; 
ENTERTAINMENT: Fun games or recreational activities; 
INFORMATIONAL: Providing information or answering questions; 
OTHER: Different purpose (specify in notes)
